		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The project will develop a glucose simulator and a model predictive controller based on work previously carried out for subjects with type 1 diabetes. Firstly, the simulator will be developed to represent glucose metabolism in subjects undergoing cardiac and thoracic surgery. Secondly, a model predictive controller will be developed and tuned using the modified simulator. The controller will take into consideration the specific conditions presen during the surgery such as large insulin resistance and fast temporal changes in insulin sensitivity. The initial stage of the clinical work will involve studying 10 subjects during surgery with the objective to collect data needed to develop the simulator. The main clinical testing will involve studying two groups of 20 subjects during surgery. One group will be treated by the controller, the control group will follow conventional treatment approach to glucose control. Clinical endpoints will be used to evaluate controller efficacy and establish the impact of normoglycaemia on post-surgical recovery.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
